data.name: Classic Meat Sauce Pork Parmesan with Lemon Zest
data.quickTastyDescription: A rich and flavorful pork meat sauce, topped with melted Parmesan and a hint of fresh lemon zest for brightness.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add diced onion and saut√© until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Stir in minced garlic and cook for another minute until fragrant.
Add the ground pork and cook until browned, breaking it apart with a spoon.
Mix in crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, salt, and pepper. Bring to a simmer.
Reduce the heat to low and let it cook for 30-40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Taste and adjust seasoning as necessary.
Once the sauce is ready, stir in the lemon zest and fresh basil just before serving.
Serve hot, topped with grated Parmesan cheese.
data.detailedName: Classic Pork Meat Sauce with Parmesan and Lemon Zest
data.modifiersForBase: Add your favorite pasta or serve over polenta for a gluten-free option.
